# Cursor AI Rules for SmartFarm Project

## File Naming Conventions
- Python files: snake_case (e.g., `main.py`, `automation.py`, `camera.py`)
- Folders: snake_case (e.g., `board_a/`, `board_b/`, `cursor_log/`, `tests/`)
- Documentation: snake_case with date-time prefix for cursor_log files
  - Format: `YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS-description.md`
  - Example: `20251230-143022-code-improvements.md`

## When creating MD files in cursor_log/
- Always use current date-time in format: YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS
- Use snake_case for description part
- Generate timestamp using: `from datetime import datetime; datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d-%H%M%S')`
- Example filename: `20251230-143022-code-improvements.md`

## Python Project Structure
- `main.py` stays at root (entry point)
- Module files (`automation.py`, `camera.py`, `logger.py`, `utils.py`) stay at root
  - This is standard for small to medium Python projects
  - All modules are imported directly by `main.py`
- Hardware-specific code: `board_a/`, `board_b/` folders
- Test files: `tests/` folder
- Documentation: `cursor_log/` folder (gitignored)

## Import Conventions
- Use absolute imports from root
- Example: `import automation`, `import camera`, `import logger`

